external_knowledge:
- Total sales volume is the sum of sales volumes across all sales records for a brand;
- Average sales volume is the mean sales volume across all sales records for a brand;
- The ranking is based on total sales volume in descending order.

- "significant sales performance" refers to brands with a total sales volume greater than 1000 (in thousands of 9-liter case depletions);
- "total sales volume" is measured in thousands of 9-liter case depletions;
- "average price" is the price per 750-ml bottle.

- "significant sales" refers to a total sales volume greater than 10,000 units;
- "units" in this context are thousands of 9-liter case depletions;
- "this year" refers to the year 2023.

sql:
SELECT brand_name
FROM brands
WHERE price_per_750ml = (SELECT MIN(price_per_750ml) FROM brands);

